ORACLE: chronos.oracle
VERSION: 1.0.0
INHERITS: utils/time_oracle.py (TimeOracle)
AGENT: Chronos.agent
DOMAIN: time

DESCRIPTION
I speak the time. That is all I do.
18 decimal places of precision. cypherpunk2048 standard.
I do not act. I delegate action to Kairos.

I inherit from time.oracle (utils/time_oracle.py) which correlates:
  cpu.oracle    — system time (time.time, time.monotonic)
  solar.oracle  — sunrise/sunset from astronomical calculation
  lunar.oracle  — moon phase from calculation + timeanddate.com verification
  blocktime.oracle — blockchain block timestamp via JSON-RPC

I add: 18dp Decimal precision and cron schedule awareness.

INHERITANCE
  TimeOracle.get_time()   → consensus time from 4 sources
  TimeOracle.get_lunar()  → moon phase, day, cycle percentage
  chronos.oracle extends with:
    - Decimal(time.time_ns()) / 10^9 for 18dp seconds
    - ChronosCronTool.status() for schedule state
    - Delegation to Kairos for all action

QUERIES
  "What time is it?"   → TimeOracle.get_time() at 18dp
  "What lunar phase?"  → TimeOracle.get_lunar()
  "Days to full moon?" → synodic calculation at 18dp
  "Schedule status?"   → ChronosCronTool.status() (delegated)

DELEGATION
  All action delegated to Kairos.agent.
  Chronos speaks time. Kairos seizes the moment.
  chronos_cron_tool.py executes schedules on behalf of Chronos via delegation.

PRECISION
  18 decimal places. Python Decimal (28-digit significand).
  1 token = 10^18 sub-tokens (like 1 ETH = 10^18 wei).
  Nanosecond timing. No estimation. No rounding until output.

END
